
# CAM-ASSIGNMENT REST API(127.0.0.1:5000)

A rest api designed to create camera and make camera networks

## Appendix

Developed using Node js, Typescript, Express js, Mongoose

 


## Authors

- [@Mohammed Ashiq](https://github.com/mohammedashiqs)


## Deployment

To deploy this project run

```bash
  npm start
```


## API Reference



## I Camera Module
-------------------

## 1. Create a camera

usage: To create camera
url: http://127.0.0.1:5000/cameras/camera
method: post
fields: name, description, url
access: private

## 2. Get all Cameras

usage: To create camera
url: http://127.0.0.1:5000/cameras/cameras
method: get
fields: no-fields
access: public


## 3. Update a camera

usage: To create camera
url: http://127.0.0.1:5000/cameras/:cameraId
method: put
fields: name, description, url
access: private


## 4. delete a camera

usage: To delete a camera
url: http://127.0.0.1:5000/cameras/:cameraId
method: delete
fields: no-fields
access: private


## 5. Get single camera

usage:Get single camera
url: http://127.0.0.1:5000/cameras/:cameraId
method: get
fields: no-fields
access: public






## II Camera Network Module
--------------------------

## 1. Get all camera Networks

usage: when click 'camera network' module, get all camera networks
url: http://127.0.0.1:5000/cameranetwork/networkcameras
method: get
fields: no-fields
Access: public 



## 2. Create a camera Network

usage: When click add 'camera network' button,
url: http://127.0.0.1:5000/cameras/camera
method: post
fields: name, description
access: private

## 3. Add cameras

usage: select one 'cameraNetwork', Click 'add camera' option, the 'camera listing page' will render, and we can select any number of cameras and click submit then redirect to that cameraNetwork and when click final submit, two array passed to server inside json objbect. [one array have the info of 'camera network' and another array have selected camera's ids] eg:- payload format: {cameras:[cam1Id, cam2Id, cam3Id], cameraNetwork:[details ofcameraNetwork]}
url:  http://127.0.0.1/cameranetworks/cameraNetwork/:cameraNetworkid
methed

